15/03/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Police used tear gas Friday (March 13th) to disperse a crowd of about 150 young anarchists who staged a riot on a commercial street in Athens. The group broke windows in dozens of shops and damaged several cars. A police officer who wished to remain anonymous said while no one was injured in the clashes, several people were arrested. During a similar riot in Thessaloniki, about 40 people damaged two bank offices and three shops. (Reuters, Xinhua, AFP, AP - 13/03/09)
